      • r

        public final Lazy<T20> r(Lazy<T> arg1)
        Description copied from class: Fun1

        Run the function.

        This method will be called by the Unknown._v() method of the lazy value returned by Fun1.a(frege.rt.Lazy<Ta>) when that lazy value is evaluated. It actually performs computation and returns a result or another lazy value that will evaluate to the result.
        It must be implemented by all subclasses.

        Once a function is instantiated, its r-method may be invoked directly. Specifically, the following identities hold: 

         f.r(x)      =  f.a(x)._v()
 f.r(x)._e() =  f.a(x)._e()
        but the expressions on the left save creation and destruction of an Unknown instance.
